## Your Task

Evaluate whether this issue is complete enough for a Claude Code worker to implement. Check the following criteria:

### 1. Title Clarity
- Is the title descriptive and actionable?
- Does it clearly indicate what needs to be done?

### 2. Description Quality
- Is there enough detail to understand the problem or feature?
- Are the requirements clearly stated?
- Can an AI understand what to implement without guessing?

### 3. Acceptance Criteria
- Are there clear acceptance criteria or success conditions?
- How will we know when this issue is "done"?

### 4. Scope Definition
- Is the scope well-defined?
- Are there clear boundaries on what's in/out of scope?
- Is the issue appropriately sized (not too large, not too vague)?

### 5. Technical Context
- Are relevant files, modules, or components mentioned?
- Are there any specific implementation hints or constraints?

